	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />&quot;All data via the coprocessor&quot; is actually the usual way it works on the SNES. (The DSP-1 is an exception)<br /><br />The S-DD1 is responsible for relaying all data, so &quot;how&quot; it locks out the ROM after a CIC fail is somewhat immaterialâ€”it could lock out arbitrary other features as well.

		

